<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-06-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-06-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Sanford</persName></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 11.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/><placeName><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-06-22"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 22, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of the 5th June, (No. 8,)
                            accompanied by a copy of your letter to Mr. De Vrière, on the subject of
                            our proposed adherence to the declaration of the congress of Paris, has
                            been received. We see no reason to doubt the propriety of that
                            communication.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Henry S. Sanford</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c., Brussels</hi>.</p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>